  "body": "I'm using **rowHeightGetter** function to dynamically change row height on state change. \nUnfortunately, after rerender rows won't position correctly. \nExpanded row gets negative offset value and Y-scroll doesn't recalculate.\n\nCalling **_updateRowHeight** method in **getRowPosition** (**FixedDataTableScrollHelper**, line 114: **this._updateRowHeight(rowIndex);**), fixes offset recalculation.\n\n``` javascript\nthis._updateRowHeight(rowIndex);\n```\n\nForcing Y-scroll recalculation by commenting lines from 634 to 636 and line 641 in **FixedDataTable.react.js**, fixes Y-scroll problem\n\n``` javascript\n//if (oldState && props.overflowY !== 'hidden') {\n//  scrollY = oldState.scrollY;\n//} else {\n   scrollState = this._scrollHelper.scrollTo(props.scrollTop);\n   firstRowIndex = scrollState.index;\n   firstRowOffset = scrollState.offset;\n   scrollY = scrollState.position;\n//}\n```\n\nI'm sure those are not most elegant solutions, added only for information purpose.\nWhats the proper solution for this problem? \n",
